**Analysis of the Target Structure**

1. **Block Count and Layers**

   - **Total Blocks:** 12  
   - **Layering (bottom‐to‐top):**  
     • **Bottom Layer:** Two red arches on the left and one small yellow plank on the far right.  
     • **Middle Layer:**  
       – A green plank bridging across the two red arches (left).  
       – A red “half‐circle” block sitting over the yellow plank (right).  
       – A second green plank spanning from the red half‐circle block to the left side.  
     • **Top Layer:**  
       – Two tall yellow pillars on top of the left green plank.  
       – Two blue cubes on top of the right green plank.  
       – Two orange triangular wedges at the far right.

2. **Spatial Relationships**  
   - The **two red arches** (side by side) form the left base.  
   - A **yellow plank** lies on the bottom at the far right, supporting the red half‐circle block above it.  
   - Each **green plank** sits horizontally: one on the arches (left), the other bridging onto the red half‐circle (right).  
   - **Two tall yellow pillars** stand side by side on the left green plank, while **two blue cubes** sit side by side on the right green plank.  
   - **Two orange wedges** adjoin the red half‐circle at the right end, creating a sloped “roof” shape.

---

**Selecting Blocks From the Dictionary**

Below are the exact dictionary indices and how many of each are needed (no extra rotations allowed):

• **Red Arches (Index 1)** – 2 needed  
• **Red Half‐Circle (Index 2)** – 1 needed  
• **Green Plank (Index 6)** – 2 needed  
• **Yellow Plank (Index 9)** – 1 needed  
• **Tall Yellow Pillar (Index 10)** – 2 needed  
• **Blue Cube (Index 4)** – 2 needed  
• **Orange Wedges (Indices 13 and 14)** – 1 each  

---

**Assembly Order**

Use the following step‐by‐step sequence (placing bottom‐layer blocks first, then building upward):

{
  Step1: Move block with index 1  
  Step2: Move block with index 1  
  Step3: Move block with index 9  
  Step4: Move block with index 2  
  Step5: Move block with index 6  
  Step6: Move block with index 6  
  Step7: Move block with index 10  
  Step8: Move block with index 10  
  Step9: Move block with index 4  
  Step10: Move block with index 4  
  Step11: Move block with index 13  
  Step12: Move block with index 14  
}

This completes the target structure exactly as shown.
